Capetown: Cape Town, South Africa; but note HMS Capetown, RMMV Capetown Castle, Capetown, California and the film Cargo to Capetown are all correct
Minesota: Minnesota; Minesota Mine [in Michigan] is correct
Monserrat: Montserrat, but see Monserrat, Buenos Aires
barron: baron; huge number of false positives
brillant: brilliant [English]; false positives for brillant [French] and Brillant [proper name]
broadcasted: broadcast should be used per WP:COMMONALITY
calender: calendar; calender is correct for the machine
cant: can not, can't, cannot; cant may be correct
cout: court, count; some false positives from C code listings
eg: e.g., egg; results in many false positives
forcasted: forecast, forecasted [non-standard past tense or past participle]
forecasted: forecast, forecasted [non-standard past tense or past participle]
grat: great, grat [Scottish past tense for greet]
hace: have, hare; mostly false positives for the Spanish word hace
heros: heroes [plural], Heros [proper name] may be correct
honourary: honorary, even in the UK and Canada - the Wiktionary entry is wrong
ottoman: Ottoman empire etc but not the furniture
peurto rico: typo to puerto rico then to caps Puerto Rico
quitted: quit, but see the usage note at wikt:quit
retuned: returned; sometimes leave as retuned or re-tuned [tuned again]
rhe: the; mostly false positives in acronyms and names
roman: Uppercase "Roman" in many contexts; but see roman type and Nouveau roman
setted: set, settled, setted [UK, of pupils or students; COD]
tarif: tariff; most are false positives for the Arab name Tarif or the French word tarif
upto: unto, up to; but see Indian English
vison: vision, part of biological classification, e.g. American mink
